records.addlTxt:
State moves to delete the penalty enhancer of second and subsequent offense on count 1.   Motion granted.    
Count 1 - Possess Morphine - No contest plea.   Convicted.   State moves to dismiss and read in count 2, possess drug paraphernalia.   Motion granted.   Sentence is withheld.   Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for eighteen (18) months.   Conditions of probation are:
1) AODA assessment and follow through; 
2) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
3) Assessment/treatment/counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
4) Maintain full-time employment/schooling combination; 
5) Spend forty-five (45) days in jail, under the Huber Law, stayed to be imposed upon the agent's discretion; 
6) Pay costs of action; 
7) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC; 
8) Submit DNA sample.   
Minutes.
